      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a strong perspective on the sociological side of things, but I'm specifically interested in the actual data being cited. If we move past the political interpretation and just look at the literature, what are the specific arguments used by proponents of the \"hereditarian\" view? I want to understand the actual points they raise regarding genetics and test scores so I can see the full picture.",
